contents.text: Single lumps can appear at any time and come in various types and sizes. Most lumps are not cancer， but your health care provider should always check the lump carefully. He or she may do more tests to make sure the lump is not cancer. See Chart 1 ： Possible Mammogram Results and Follow-Up Care (page 26) for more information about these types of lumps.
